data.title: The George and Barbara Bush Distinguished Lecture Series is an inspiring and informative event that I look forward to each fall semester....
data.meta_description:
179 likes, 1 comments - james.herbert on September 29, 2023: "The George and Barbara Bush Distinguished Lecture Series is an inspiring and informative event that I look forward to each fall semester. On Wednesday, guests gathered to hear The Honorable John H. Sununu, former chief of staff to President George H.W. Bush - as moderated by The Honorable Andrew H. Card, Jr., former chief of staff to President George W. Bush - discuss the Indispensable Bush Presidency.

Thank you to the George and Barbara Bush Foundation (@bushfdn) for maintaining the Bush legacy of unwavering connection to the UNE community. We are grateful for your support!".
